# Authentication Flows

The DocuVault API supports two authentication methods:

## JWT Authentication Flow
1. Generate a challenge: `POST /api/v1/auth/jwt/generate-challenge`
2. Sign the challenge with the user's wallet
3. Authenticate: `POST /api/v1/auth/jwt/authenticate`
4. Store tokens for authenticated requests
5. Refresh token when needed: `POST /api/v1/auth/jwt/refresh`

## SIWE Authentication Flow
1. Obtain a nonce: `GET /api/v1/auth/siwe/nonce`
2. Create and sign a SIWE message
3. Verify the message: `POST /api/v1/auth/siwe/verify`
4. Make authenticated requests using the token
5. Refresh when needed: `POST /api/v1/auth/siwe/refresh`
6. Logout when done: `POST /api/v1/auth/siwe/logout`

